President Muhammadu Buhari will be departing Abuja today for the capital of Cote D’Ivoire, Abidjan, to the 15th session of the Conference Of the Parties (COP15) of the United Nations Convention to Combat Desertification (UNCCD).   Senator Arthur Nzeribe dies at 83     Wives of Vice-Chancellors postpone UNILAG conference     Editors take self-scrutiny town hall meeting to Port…   According to a statement issued by Presidential spokesman, Mallam Garba Shehu, the event, themed ‘Land. Life. Legacy: From scarcity to prosperity’, will focus on the future of land, regarding desertification, drought, degradation, rights, restoration and implications for national and world economies.